source_text: What is the document id and name with greatest number of paragraphs?
target_text: SELECT documents, PROJECT paragraphs of #REF #1, GROUP count #2 #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is the greatest, PROJECT the document id of #REF #4, PROJECT the name of #REF #4, UNION #5 #6

source_text: Return the id and name of the document with the most paragraphs.
target_text: SELECT documents, PROJECT paragraphs in #REF #1, GROUP count #2 #1, SUPERLATIVE max #1 #3, PROJECT id of #REF #4, PROJECT name of #REF #4, UNION #5 #6

source_text: What is the document id with least number of paragraphs?
target_text: SELECT document ids, PROJECT paragraphs #1, GROUP count #2 #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is the least

source_text: Return the id of the document with the fewest paragraphs.
target_text: SELECT documents, PROJECT paragraphs of #REF #1, GROUP count #2 #1, SUPERLATIVE min #1 #3, PROJECT id of #REF #4

source_text: What is the document id with 1 to 2 paragraphs?
target_text: SELECT documents, PROJECT paragraphs of #REF #1, GROUP count #2 #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is at least 1, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is at most 2, SELECT document id, INTERSECTION #6 #4 #5

source_text: Give the ids of documents that have between one and two paragraphs.
target_text: SELECT documents, PROJECT paragraphs of #REF #1, GROUP count #2 #1, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is at least one, COMPARATIVE #1 #3 is at most two, INTERSECTION #1 #4 #5, PROJECT ids of #REF #6

source_text: Show the document id with paragraph text 'Brazil' and 'Ireland'.

source_text: What are the names of the singers who performed in a concert in 2014?
